# dozenos-rebrand top-level .gitignore
#
# This is belt-and-suspenders on top of keys/.gitignore (which contains a
# bare `*` and already excludes everything under keys/, including itself).
# Do NOT remove the keys/ rule below even though it looks redundant -- two
# independent ignore rules make an accidental `git add -f keys/...` far less
# likely to succeed silently.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Real throwaway-dev private key material -- NEVER publish.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/keys/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Editor / OS / VCS cruft.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Transient build/test output.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.tmp
*.log
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# release/make-ephemeral-apt-repo.sh, sign-and-publish.sh, mirror-push.sh,
# and several test/*.sh scripts default their scratch/output dirs to
# `mktemp -d` (out-of-tree, under /tmp) -- they do not create in-tree scratch
# directories by default. The entries below only guard against someone
# invoking a script's `--work <dir>` / `--out-dir <dir>` override to point
# in-tree, so a stray local run can never get committed.
/scratch/
/.scratch/
/work/
/*.scratch/
